From 622c27743f69f3690e3bd1aa7766cfbd4e03b53f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vasu Bhatia <git@vbh.ai>
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 2026 23:57:44 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 20/21] eink: whitespace-only notifications + group thread bar
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace the earlier rounded-card-with-border attempt for notifications
with a whitespace-only flat list. AOSP applies flat corner radii to
"stacked" rows beyond just group children — section boundaries and
visually adjacent independents — so a card-border approach kept
producing half-rounded or square shapes that read as broken with our
explicit chrome. Drop the chrome entirely.

Behaviour:
  - Independent notifications get NO chrome at all. Separation comes
    purely from AOSP's existing notification_divider_height row
    spacing, like paragraphs in a magazine.
  - Group children draw a 2dp vertical black bar inset 24dp from the
    left edge, full row height. The 24dp inset places the bar in the
    gutter between the parent icon column and the child text content
    (notification_content_margin_start = 72dp), so the line visually
    drops from beneath the parent's icon down through the indented
    children — like an email-thread or code-fold marker.

Implementation:
  - NotificationBackgroundView gets an mEinkLinePaint, two cached
    dp-to-px constants (2dp bar width, 24dp left inset) and an
    mIsChildInGroup flag with a setIsChildInGroup setter. The new
    drawEinkOverlay helper draws the bar when the flag is set.
  - drawEinkOverlay is called from BOTH branches of onDraw (legacy
    and new dismiss-on-hover) so the bar appears regardless of the
    NotificationAddXOnHoverToDismiss flag state.
  - ActivatableNotificationView.updateBackgroundClipping plumbs
    isChildInGroup() to mBackgroundNormal alongside the existing
    setBottomAmountClips call.

The corner radii AOSP sets via setRadius become invisible — there's
no fill differentiation between row and shade (both white) and no
border to be clipped, so rounded-vs-square corners on the underlying
shape don't show. Colorized notifications (media, app-tinted) keep
their rounded edges since their fill colour differs from the shade.

Change-Id: Ic2bf1bacb83a066f72b6064aa4c235a720c4ac3d
